  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: edge-case coverage gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: COU explicitly names high-shear-stress impeller-tip regions and low-flow near-stall operating points as required evaluation targets; validation results cover only the nominal 2–5 L/min mid-speed range and do not include those edge cases.",
